Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a distributed differential space time coding scheme and analyzes the pairwise error probability and block error rate, which are key concepts in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with two-way relay networks and proposes an analog network coding scheme, which is a networking concept.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system for signal transmission and reception in two-way relay networks, which falls under the systems and control category.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with signal processing and transmission, which is a key concept in multimedia.
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - Although less likely, the paper may fall under the computers and society category as it deals with the impact of technology on communication and networking.
